      • OpenAddPartMenu

        public void OpenAddPartMenu​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        Opens up the Add Part Menu Error Exception happens if the Part menu does not exist or if the program is unable to open the Form up. This causes the application to stall and not proceed any farther as there is no window for the user to return to.
        Parameters:
        event - Changes the Stage to Add Part Menu if unable to open Add Part Menu an alert pops up alerting the user that system was unable to open up the menu.

      • OpenAddProductMenu

        public void OpenAddProductMenu​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)

        Parameters:

      • onActionModifyPart

        public void onActionModifyPart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        Opens Modify Part Menu and completes the form with the data selected Error Exception happens when the does not select a part to modify
        Parameters:
        event - Allows the user to select a part to add and changes the scene to the Modify Part Menu

      • ExitMenu

        public void ExitMenu()
        An alert pops up alerting the user with a confirmation message. If the user selects okay, the program will close if the user selects cancel, the alert message will close and user is returned to Main Window.

      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle rb)
        Initializes the Table View. The second table view is populated will parts that are being associated with the product.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - points to the Specified tag, ID, Name, Price, Stock
        rb - populates the tableviews with information gained from Inventory.getAllParts. Sets the parts of the items by matching id, name, price, stock to the columns.
